<subSubSection id="C89655E1E34F805AFF70FF3C4630FE97" pageId="4" pageNumber="1647" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8033066AE34F805AFF70FF3C4630FE97" blockId="4.[178,1085,220,303]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1647">Etymology: The specific epithet (Latin, adjective: mutilated, deficient) alludes to the asymmetric ventral process of the aedeagus, as well as to other asymmetries in the male and female sexual characters.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C89655E1E34F805AFF70FEDF4701FA65" pageId="4" pageNumber="1647" type="description">
<paragraph id="8033066AE34F805AFF70FEDF4509FE14" blockId="4.[178,1086,319,428]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1647">
Description: Species of moderate size; body length 5.5-8.0 mm; length of forebody 
<quantity id="4774AB8FE34F805AFF2EFEBC4540FECA" box="[236,356,348,370]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" metricValueMax="3.6" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="1647" unit="mm" value="3.4" valueMax="3.6" valueMin="3.2">3.2-3.6 mm</quantity>
. For a colour image of the habitus see figure 2B in 
<bibRefCitation id="E41D7B9BE34F805AFCB3FEBD401DFECA" author="PENG Z &amp; LI L" box="[881,1081,348,370]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1647" pagination="21 - 32" refId="ref6557" refString="PENG Z., LI L. - Z. &amp; M. - J. ZHAO (2012 a): Taxonomic study on Lathrobium GRAVENHORST (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Paederinae) from Longwangshan Mountain, East China. - ZooKeys 165: 21 - 32." type="journal article" year="2012">PENG et al. (2012a)</bibRefCitation>
. Coloration: body dark-brown to blackish-brown; legs and antennae dark-reddish to reddish-brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8033066AE34F805AFF70FE5C4692FDFF" blockId="4.[178,1085,444,583]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1647">Head 1.05-1.10 times as broad as long, slightly dilated posteriad; punctation moderately coarse and moderately dense, sparser in postero-median dorsal portion; interstices with shallow microreticulation. Eyes weakly projecting from lateral contours of head, approximately 0.4 times as long as postocular region in dorsal view and composed of about 40-50 ommatidia. Antenna 1.8-2.0 mm long.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8033066AE34F805AFF70FDB746B5FD1F" blockId="4.[178,1085,598,679]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1647">Pronotum approximately 1.2 times as long as broad and slightly broader than head, slightly tapering posteriad; punctation similar to that of head; impunctate midline moderately broad; interstices without microsculpture.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8033066AE34F805AFF70FD5645F2FC9C" blockId="4.[178,1086,694,804]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1647">Elytra short, 0.51-0.54 times as long as pronotum, very weakly dilated posteriad; humeral angles moderately marked; punctation rather dense and defined; interstices without microsculpture. Hind wings completely reduced. Protarsomeres I-IV with pronounced sexual dimorphism.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8033066AE34F805AFF70FCD34517FC19" blockId="4.[178,1086,819,929]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1647">Abdomen 1.05-1.10 times as broad as elytra; punctation fine and dense, somewhat less dense on tergites VII and VIII; interstices with very fine and shallow microsculpture; posterior margin of tergite VII without palisade fringe; tergite VIII with distinct sexual dimorphism.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8033066AE34F805AFF05FC514561FA9D" blockId="4.[178,1086,944,1317]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1647">
: protarsomeres I-IV strongly dilated; tergite VIII with convex posterior margin; sternite VII (
<figureCitation id="18B71AEFE34F805AFED5FC2D4573FC5B" box="[279,343,973,995]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="5.[178,218,1512,1532]" captionTargetBox="[183,1067,223,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-47@5.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 1-8: Lathrobium rougemonti, holotype (1-4) and L. mancum (5-8): (1, 5) male sternite VII; (2, 6) male sternite VIII; (3-4, 7-8) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6514327" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6514327/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1647">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) strongly transverse, posteriorly with median impression of triangular shape, this impression with cluster of about 30 distinctly modified, short and stout black setae, posterior margin concave in the middle; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="18B71AEFE34F805AFCDCFBE8477FFBA6" box="[798,859,1032,1054]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="5.[178,218,1512,1532]" captionTargetBox="[183,1067,223,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-47@5.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 1-8: Lathrobium rougemonti, holotype (1-4) and L. mancum (5-8): (1, 5) male sternite VII; (2, 6) male sternite VIII; (3-4, 7-8) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6514327" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6514327/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1647">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) distinctly transverse, approximately 1.2 times as broad as long, with pronounced, extensive, and somewhat asymmetric median impression, this impression with numerous distinctly modified, short and stout black setae, posterior margin convex with a small concave excision in the middle; aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="18B71AEFE34F805AFE8FFB9D4580FB2B" box="[333,420,1149,1171]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="5.[178,218,1512,1532]" captionTargetBox="[183,1067,223,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-47@5.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 1-8: Lathrobium rougemonti, holotype (1-4) and L. mancum (5-8): (1, 5) male sternite VII; (2, 6) male sternite VIII; (3-4, 7-8) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6514327" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6514327/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1647">Figs 7-8</figureCitation>
) approximately 
<quantity id="4774AB8FE34F805AFD92FB9D46BBFB2B" box="[592,671,1149,1171]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="4" pageNumber="1647" unit="mm" value="1.1">1.1 mm</quantity>
long and distinctly asymmetric; ventral process stout, strongly sclerotized, and apically acute, left side with tooth-like projection in ventral view; dorsal plate lamellate, with long and weakly sclerotized apical portion and with short, indistinct basal portion; internal sac with two large, plate-like, and apically spine-shaped and prominent sclerotized structures, and with a cluster of short sclerotized spines.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8033066AE34F805AFF05FAD54701FA65" blockId="4.[178,1086,1333,1501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1647">
: protarsomeres I-IV moderately dilated, distinctly less so than in male; posterior margin of tergite VIII obtusely produced in the middle; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="18B71AEFE34F805AFC4FFAB247F8FAD0" box="[909,988,1362,1384]" captionStart="Figs 9-18" captionStartId="6.[178,218,1512,1532]" captionTargetBox="[178,1073,212,1492]" captionTargetId="figure-77@6.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 9-18: Lathrobium barbiventre (9-10), L. rougemonti (11), L. mancum (12-13), and L. bicuspidatum (14-18): (9, 12) female sternite VIII; (10, 11, 13) female tergites IX-X; (14) forebody; (15) male sternite VII; (16) male sternite VIII; (17-18) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 14: 1.0 mm; 9-13, 15-18: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303205" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303205/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1647">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) oblong, approximately 1.15 times as long as broad, posteriorly convexly produced in the middle; tergite IX (
<figureCitation id="18B71AEFE34F805AFEECFA6C455AFA1A" box="[302,382,1420,1442]" captionStart="Figs 9-18" captionStartId="6.[178,218,1512,1532]" captionTargetBox="[178,1073,212,1492]" captionTargetId="figure-77@6.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 9-18: Lathrobium barbiventre (9-10), L. rougemonti (11), L. mancum (12-13), and L. bicuspidatum (14-18): (9, 12) female sternite VIII; (10, 11, 13) female tergites IX-X; (14) forebody; (15) male sternite VII; (16) male sternite VIII; (17-18) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 14: 1.0 mm; 9-13, 15-18: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303205" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303205/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1647">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
) asymmetric, antero-median portion very short and with median suture; tergite X (
<figureCitation id="18B71AEFE34F805AFEA4FA4A4594FA78" box="[358,432,1450,1472]" captionStart="Figs 9-18" captionStartId="6.[178,218,1512,1532]" captionTargetBox="[178,1073,212,1492]" captionTargetId="figure-77@6.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 9-18: Lathrobium barbiventre (9-10), L. rougemonti (11), L. mancum (12-13), and L. bicuspidatum (14-18): (9, 12) female sternite VIII; (10, 11, 13) female tergites IX-X; (14) forebody; (15) male sternite VII; (16) male sternite VIII; (17-18) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 14: 1.0 mm; 9-13, 15-18: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303205" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303205/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1647">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
) weakly asymmetric, weakly convex in cross-section, and more than five times as long as antero-median portion of tergite IX.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
