<subSubSection id="C89655E1E34C8059FF70FF394786FDC7" pageId="7" pageNumber="1650" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8033066AE34C8059FF70FF394597FDBF" blockId="7.[178,1085,217,519]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1650">
Comparative notes: As can be inferred from the similarly derived shapes and chaetotaxy of the male sternites VII and VIII, the similarly derived morphology of the aedeagus, as well as from the similarly asymmetric female tergites IX and X, 
<taxonomicName id="478C7DE9E34C8059FBEAFEF2452CFEFB" authorityName="Assing &amp; S" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1650" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mancum">
<emphasis id="B2F8DA78E34C8059FBEAFEF2452CFEFB" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1650">L. mancum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is undoubtedly the adelphotaxon of the geographically close 
<taxonomicName id="478C7DE9E34C8059FC4EFECE403AFEFB" authorityName=", Y. Watanabe" authorityYear="1999" box="[908,1054,302,323]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1650" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rougemonti">
<emphasis id="B2F8DA78E34C8059FC4EFECE403AFEFB" box="[908,1054,302,323]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1650">L. rougemonti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It differs from this species by the shape of the posterior cluster of modified setae on the male sternite VII, the more transverse male sternite VIII with a less broad median impression, the slightly shorter aedeagus (
<taxonomicName id="478C7DE9E34C8059FDA8FE6246D8FE2F" authorityName=", Y. Watanabe" authorityYear="1999" box="[618,764,386,407]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1650" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rougemonti">
<emphasis id="B2F8DA78E34C8059FDA8FE6246D8FE2F" box="[618,764,386,407]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1650">L. rougemonti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: length of aedeagus 
<quantity id="4774AB8FE34C8059FC1AFE614012FE2F" box="[984,1078,385,407]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" pageId="7" pageNumber="1650" unit="mm" value="1.15">1.15 mm</quantity>
) with a stouter and shorter ventral process with a tooth-shaped projection on the left side (ventral view) and with internal structures of different shape, by the posteriorly slightly more distinctly produced female sternite VIII, and by the less strongly asymmetric female tergites IX and X.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8033066AE34C8059FF70FDF54786FDC7" blockId="7.[178,1086,533,639]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1650">
Comment: 
<bibRefCitation id="E41D7B9BE34C8059FEA7FDF6460BFD93" author="PENG Z &amp; LI L" box="[357,559,533,555]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1650" pagination="21 - 32" refId="ref6557" refString="PENG Z., LI L. - Z. &amp; M. - J. ZHAO (2012 a): Taxonomic study on Lathrobium GRAVENHORST (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Paederinae) from Longwangshan Mountain, East China. - ZooKeys 165: 21 - 32." type="journal article" year="2012">PENG et al. (2012a)</bibRefCitation>
illustrated the external and sexual characters of 
<taxonomicName id="478C7DE9E34C8059FBEAFDF6452CFDFF" authorityName="Assing &amp; S" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1650" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mancum">
<emphasis id="B2F8DA78E34C8059FBEAFDF6452CFDFF" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1650">L. mancum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on material from the Longwang Shan (as 
<taxonomicName id="478C7DE9E34C8059FD39FDD147BEFDFF" box="[763,922,561,583]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1650" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B2F8DA78E34C8059FD39FDD14756FDFF" box="[763,882,561,583]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1650">Lathrobium</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
; figures 2B and 7). However, without a revision of the 
<typeStatus id="5F37B8C8E34C8059FD83FDAE4649FDDB" box="[577,621,590,611]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1650">type</typeStatus>
material of the highly similar 
<taxonomicName id="478C7DE9E34C8059FC64FDAE4013FDDB" authorityName=", Y. Watanabe" authorityYear="1999" box="[934,1079,590,611]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1650" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rougemonti">
<emphasis id="B2F8DA78E34C8059FC64FDAE4013FDDB" box="[934,1079,590,611]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1650">L. rougemonti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it was not possible to assess with certainty if both were conspecific or not.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C89655E1E34C8059FF70FD6D46B3FCAB" pageId="7" pageNumber="1650" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8033066AE34C8059FF70FD6D46B3FCAB" blockId="7.[178,1086,653,787]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1650">
Distribution and natural history: The 
<typeStatus id="5F37B8C8E34C8059FC8FFD6E4755FD1B" box="[845,881,654,675]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1650">type</typeStatus>
material was collected both in the Tianmu Shan and the Longwang Shan in 
